OL,3,C'I was tricked into breaking the law':
OL,4,CMan lured into being a 'money mule'
OL,6,FA man who was used as a 'money mule'
OL,7,Fsays he was tricked by criminals
OL,8,Fonline promising 'easy money'.
OL,10,FMoney muling involves criminals using
OL,11,Fsomeone else's bank account to move
OL,12,Fstolen or illicit funds, helping to
OL,13,Fdisguise where the money has come
OL,14,Ffrom. The 'mules' typically keep a
OL,15,Fsmall share of the cash, often without
OL,16,Ffully understanding the consequences.
OL,18,FAccording to figures from Lloyds Bank,
OL,19,Fcases in Wales rose by 104% last year
OL,20,F- the largest increase recorded
OL,21,Fanywhere in the UK.
