OL,3,C'I was tricked into breaking the law':
OL,4,CMan lured into being a 'money mule'
OL,6,FWhen Darren received a private message
OL,7,Fasking if he would transfer the sum of
OL,8,F#80 into his account, he says he
OL,9,Fdidn't question it. He was then asked
OL,10,Fto transfer #55 onto someone else, and
OL,11,Fcould keep #25 as payment.
OL,13,F"I was vulnerable...I just thought it
OL,14,Fwas a way of making some extra money"
OL,15,Fhe says.
OL,17,FOver time, Darren was offered more
OL,18,Fmoney to recruit others and even to
OL,19,Fsell his bank accounts to the
OL,20,Fcriminals.
